<HEADLINE> French President Meets Russian Parliamentary Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Visiting French President
Jacques Chirac today met with the leaders of Russian parliamentary
groups - Alexander Shokhin from "Our Home is Russia" and Gennady
Zyuganov from "the Communist Party of the Russian Federation", the
Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Chirac discussed the Russia's new tax code
with the leaders, which is considered by foreign financiers as a
crucial precondition for further investment, the agency
said.
</P>
<P>
Focusing on the political situation in Russia and
Russian-French cooperation, Shokhin held that not enough French
capital is being invested in Russia, and hoped that their joint
projects in the oil-and-gas and timber industries will progress as
expected.
</P>
<P>
Zyuganov, on his part, said France is "a strategic ally" of
Russia and vowed to further develop the bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Chirac arrived here for a three-day official visit on Thursday
and is expected to leave for St. Petersburg today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
