<HEADLINE> Tunisia, Czech Republic to Enhance Military Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Visiting defence minister of
Tunisia Habib Ben Yahia told his Czech counterpart Miloslav
Vyborny here today that Tunisia wanted to strengthen military
cooperation with the Czech Republic, particularly in the fields of
ammunition and training.
</P>
<P>
Yahia made the remarks to the press after talks with Vyborny.
</P>
<P>
Apart from buying more Czech-produced L-59 and L-410 planes,
Tunisia is also interested in Czech Republic's air defense and
radar equipment and "Tatra" heavy-duty trucks, he said.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Yahia also met with Czech chairman of the
Chamber of Deputies Milos Zeman and Minister of Foreign Affairs
Josef Zieleniec.
</P>
<P>
Yahia arrived here on September 25 for a three-day official
visit. 
</P>
