<HEADLINE> Mozambique's Gorongosa National Park Reopens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique's Gorongosa
National Park in the central province of Sofala reopened today
temporarily after many years of closure, the Mozambique News
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The opening ceremony was presided by Mozambican Prime
Minister Pascoal Mocumbi who flied from Maputo, the
capital, to Beira, capital city of Sofala province for the
occasion.
</P>
<P>
Gorongosa Park is known for its beautiful natural landscape,
large forest, as well as animal and plant resources. The park
was shut up at the end of 1970s, and became one of the main
battle fields during the country's 16-year-long civil war.
</P>
<P>
In the recent years, with domestic and foreign aid, the
Mozambican government has made great efforts in re-opening the
park, especially in terms of landmine clearance.
</P>
<P>
According to Beatriz de Sousa, head of the provincial Bureau
of Industry, Trade and Tourism in Sofala, the Mozambican
government will soon call for tenders for rehabilitating
infrastructure in the parkto promote tourism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
