<DOCNO> XIE19970928.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OAU Chief Urged U.N. to Focus on Peace, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Salim Ahmed Salim,
Secretary-General of the Organization of African Unity (OAU) has
appealed to the U.N. to attach great importance to peace,
stability and economic development in Africa, an OAU press
release said today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the first ministerial meeting of the U.N. Security
Council Friday in New York, Salim said conflicts cause
irreparable loss, damage and destruction to the African continent
and its people, leading to acute humanitarian tragedies.
</P>
<P>
On the urgent need for the elimination of the root causes of
humanitarian crisis in Africa, Salim said the United Nations and
the OAU should learn from the failure to anticipate and
effectively prevent the crime of genocide in Rwanda which
resulted in the decimation of hundreds of thousands of human
beings.
</P>
<P>
The OAU chief urged the United Nations and the OAU to learn
from the inability of the Security Council to respond
appropriately to the call by African leaders to deal with the
crisis in the eastern part of former Zaire.
</P>
<P>
He called for the forging ahead of a new and true partnership
that can enable the two bodies to address together in a sustained
manner the acute problems facing Africa.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the question of conflicts, Salim said the U.N.
and the OAU should pay more attention to preventive diplomacy
and preventive deployment in Africa and help build a joint capacity
for post conflict reconstruction and peace-building.
</P>
<P>
Salim also called on the U.N. to provide the OAU with the
necessary logistical and technical assistance that is needed to
enhance the organizations' capacity to respond to conflict
situations, the press release added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
