<HEADLINE> Fire Burns 5,000 Acres, 20 Homes in California </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 28 (Xinhua) -- A wild fire started
Saturday night in northern California, burning more than 5,000
acres of bush and forest and 20 homes.
</P>
<P>
About 1,000 people were forced to flee their homes during the
night as the wind-driven fire raced through a heavily forested
area, state forestry officials said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Nearly all of the residents of the small towns of Dobbins and
Oregon House had to leave, officials of the California Department
of Forestry said.
</P>
<P>
About 1,400 firefighters were dispatched and air tankers,
helicopters and bulldozers were used to fight the fire that
started in the mountainous Grass Valley region of northern
California. 
</P>
