is in the fourth place in the candidates' popularity ratings. He
took second place in the TV debates, attracting 17.7 percent of
television viewers Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Former Kyonggi Governor Rhee In-je, in second-place in the
popularity polls, took third place in the viewers' ratings, with
17.2 percent. He appeared on the MBC debate as the lead-off
candidate Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ruling party candidate Lee Hoi-chang, whose popularity rating
puts him in third place after Kim Dae-jung and Rhee, took fourth
place in the viewers' ratings, with 16.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
