<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Lincoln National, as one of
the leading insurers in the United States, hopes to open its China
business at an early date, Stephen Meldrum, president of its China
company said.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a recent seminar on Sino-US insurance cooperation
here, Meldrum described China's insurance market as one with the
largest potential and fastest growth in the world.
</P>
<P>
Lincoln National sponsored the two-day seminar, and was one of
the co-organizers along with the Volunteers of America and the
Tianjin Insurers' Association.
</P>
<P>
Discussions on life insurance theory and practices were
conducted among insurance institution leaders, financial officials
and scholars of universities and research institutes from a dozen
Chinese provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities, and
specialists from Lincoln National.
</P>
<P>
This was the fourth seminar of its kind sponsored and organized
by Lincoln National. Training courses in the US were also offered
to senior managers of China's insurance industry.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, according to Meldrum, the corporation has made a
direst or indirect investment of more than 80 million US dollars
in China.  
