<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng met recently
with Chinese master artists and craftsmen and asked them to
inherit, carry forward and improve on the fine traditional styles
and techniques.
</P>
<P>
Li said that they should "weed through the old and bring out
the new" to develop products with characteristics in accordance
with the times.
</P>
<P>
The Light Industry Association today bestowed the title of
Chinese Master of Arts and Crafts on 108 people well-accomplished
in their fields.
</P>
<P>
The premier said that arts and crafts are an important
component of the fine Chinese culture as well as a treasure of the
the world civilization.
</P>
<P>
"Since the founding of New China in 1949, especially since the
reform and opening in 1970's, the arts and crafts industry has
contributed actively to international exchanges, inheriting and
carrying forth the fine traditional culture of the nation," he
said. The industry also has been strongly pushing the the course
of building socialist material civilization as well as socialist
ethical and cultural progress.
</P>
<P>
In line with the improved living standard of the people and the
growth of tourism, Li said the arts and crafts market will become
increasingly bigger and bigger, and that people should improve the
products' quality by relying on the advanced technical-how and
develop products that suit the customers' tastes.
</P>
<P>
The premier urged that a state decree concerning the protection
of the industry be followed and that a workforce be trained to
make even greater contributions to the sector.  
</P>
