<HEADLINE> Ethiopia's Three Lakes Threatened by Siltation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, Septemebr 28 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's three rift
valley lakes, Ziway, Abiyata and Langano, are becoming a meter
shallower annually due to siltation resulting from sever erosion
of the lakes' catchment areas.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency reported today quoted local
officials from the natural resources conservation and development
offices and residents as saying this.
</P>
<P>
Uncontrolled felling of the acasia trees in the surrounding
areas has been responsible for the erosion and the resultant
siltation, they said.
</P>
<P>
The three lakes have a combined depth of 51 meters.
</P>
<P>
Local officials said the preservation of the lakes is not a
task entirely left to a single office alone. They called on local
residents to take part in the conservation effort. 
</P>
</TEXT>
