The New York Times
</P>
<P>
-- Republican leaders have begun a push for a radical revision
of the tax code, but the party has yet to reach a consensus about
what kind of changes it wants to see. The shift in focus comes as
pollsters report that voters are becoming cynical about promises
of tax cuts.
