<P>
The Washington Post
</P>
<P>
-- According to President Clinton's playbook, this fall was
supposed to be a season of bipartisan achievement on the issue of
free trade: Republican congressional leaders would deliver their
members, Clinton would deliver moderate Democrats, and together
they would have the votes to overcome the opposition of organized
labor and pass a "fast-track" trade bill. 
</P>
</TEXT>
