<HEADLINE> China's Second Round of Treasury Bonds Completed Ahead of Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- China finished its second
treasury bonds issue for this year by September 20, the Ministry
of Finance announced today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 128.455 billion yuan worth of certificate bonds were
sold between March 1 and September 20.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry said the final bond offering was completed a month
ahead of schedule thanks to joint efforts of the issuing banks,
including the People's Bank of China, Agricultural Bank of China,
Bank of China, China Construction Bank and Bank of Communications,
and departments of the Ministry of Finance.
</P>
<P>
The smooth sale of certificate bonds provided useful funds for
budgetary purposes and made the macro-economic control goals more
attainable, the Ministry of Finance said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, in order to enable more people to buy treasury bonds,
sales networks have been extended for the additional 40 billion
yuan worth of certificate bonds that was issued from September 1.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
