<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria beat Cameroun 3-1
Saturday night in an African Zone Group B match of the Men's World
Volleyball Qualification Tournament in Kano, north Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria scored a 15-9, 15-11, 9-15, 15-10 victory after a 0-3
loss to Egypt Friday, according to the Nigerian Volleyball
Association.
</P>
