ten seconds faster than the year's previous best time set by
Portugal's Domingos Castro at the Rotterdam Marathon.
</P>
<P>
Eric Kimaiyo finished second in 2:07:43 and Sammy Lelei was the
third in 2:07:54. Their compatriot Jackson Kipngok was the fourth,
timing 2:08:31.
</P>
<P>
For the women, Irish Catherina McKiernan, 27, claimed the title
in her debut in this event, setting a course record of 2:23:44.
</P>
<P>
Madina Biktagirova of Belarus was the second with a time of
2:24:46 with Marllen Renders of Belgium third at 2:26:18. 
