<HEADLINE> PLA to Open Barracks in Hong Kong for National Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The Garrison of the
People's Liberation Army (PLA) stationed in the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) will open its barracks to the public
on October 1, the National Day.
</P>
<P>
Groups will be allowed to tour camps at Stanley and
Stonecutters Island and visit gunboats, according to a statement
issued by the garrison.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first time since Hong Kong's return to the
motherland on July 1 that local residents have been allowed
inside the garrison's military bases and also marks the first
National Day celebrations by PLA forces in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The garrison troops will stage cultural shows, basketball
matches and other activities on their open day.
</P>
<P>
The two camps will be open between 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. in two
sessions to receive up to 40 groups and organizations each
including up to 50 people, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
It stressed that the open day is aimed at improving
communications and understanding between the garrison troops and
the general public.
</P>
<P>
"There will be a morning and an afternoon session and we shall
receive 20 groups at most in each session," a spokesman for the
garrison told reporters this morning.
</P>
<P>
"We think that it is good enough as the forces have only been
stationed here for three months and there might not be too many
things to see," he added. 
</P>
