<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA -- A tectonic earthquake measuring 6 on the Richter
scale shocked counties of Kodya Pare-Pare and Pinrang in South
Sulawesi Province, Indonesia, Sunday, killing 12 people and
injuring dozens of others, Antara News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake, which occurred at 8:38 a.m. local
time, was located some 20 kilometers north of Kodya Pare-Pare.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of houses and six cars were also destroyed in the
quake, the report said. (Indonesia-Quake-Deaths)
