working at partial capacity, the city government said.
</P>
<P>
The Metropolitan Environment Commission made the decision
Saturday afternoon as ozone levels went above allowable readings.
</P>
<P>
Under the emergency rules, half of the city's vehicles will be
pulled from the road, while factories are only allowed to work at
30-40 percent of capacity. One fifth of the gas stations will be
shut down and all outdoor sports activities will be called off in
schools. (Mexico-Pollution-Emergency)
