<HEADLINE> Tectonic Quake Kills 12 People in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 28 (Xinhua) -- A tectonic earthquake
measuring 6 on the Richter scale shocked counties of Kodya
Pare-Pare and Pinrang in South Sulawesi Province, Indonesia,
today, killing 12 people and injuring dozens of others, Antara
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake, which occurred at 8:38 a.m. local
time, was located some 20 kilometers north of Kodya Pare-Pare.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of houses and six cars were also destroyed in the
quake, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 12 who died, six are villagers of Kodya Pare-Pare and
the others from Pinrang.
</P>
<P>
According to M. Adnan, a resident in Kodya Pare-Pare, the quake
only lasted several seconds, but a number of buildings were
destroyed.
</P>
<P>
The people who were injured seriously had been sent to
hospitals nearby, the report added.  
