<HEADLINE> South Korea Beat Japan in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 28 (Xinhua) -- South Korea beat Japan 2-1 in a
World Cup qualifier between the two co-hosts of the 2002 World Cup
finals here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
It was South korea's third straight victory and they now lead
the group with nine points. The United Arab Emirates beat
Uzbekistan to place second in the group with 7 points from two
wins and one draw.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's match, the two teams played to a goalless draw in
the first half. It was the Japanese team which broke the deadlock
when Motohiro Yamaguchi sent home a looping shot over South Korean
goal-keeper Kim Byung-Ji.
</P>
<P>
After taking the 1-0 lead, the Japanese team concentrated more
on defense and that gave the South Korean team a chance of
fighting back.
</P>
<P>
Seo Jung-Won headed home the equalizer in the 83rd minute while
Lee Min-Sung made it 2-1 for the South Korean team after receiving
a pass from the right just in front of the Japanese goal.
</P>
<P>
The defeat leaves Japan in the third place of the group with 4
points from one win, one draw and one loss. The group also
includes Uzbekistan and Kazakhstan. 
</P>
