<HEADLINE> 11 Million Child Workers in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 28 (Xinhua) -- There are nearly 11 million
child workers in the age group of 5-14 years throughout India, a
local newspaper, The Hindustan Times, said here today.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 6 million are males and 5 million females. These,
however, exclude the number of child workers in the
India-controlled Jammu and Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 80 percent of the child workers were categorized as
"main workers" as against "marginal workers" and "non-workers,"
the paper said.
</P>
<P>
And they account for 5.4 percent of the total population in
this age group.
</P>
<P>
A little more than 42 percent of the non-workers among males
are students.  
