<HEADLINE> China to Host First Art Festival on Yu Opera </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The First Art Festival on
Yu Opera, a local art form popular in central China is to be held
in this capital city of the province from October 6-14.
</P>
<P>
Henan, the birthplace of Yu Opera, will host 14 art troupes
from Hubei, Shandong, Gansu, Shaanxi, Anhui, and Henan Province,
and Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region during the eight-day festival.
</P>
<P>
The performers will stage a variety of Yu Opera, including 16
repertoires of new stories. Meanwhile, artists nationwide will
exchange opinions on the development of the art form in a number
of symposia.
</P>
<P>
Yu Opera came into being in the middle of the Qing Dynasty
(1644-1911) and is one of the four leading operas in China. To
date, 220 Yu Opera art troupes have been formed covering 16
provinces and regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
