<HEADLINE> Charity Organization Founded in Lanzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Lanzhou Charity Federation
has recently been founded in this capital city of northwest
China's Gansu province, Beijing-based China Society News reported.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the federation is to aid the 160,000 impoverished
population and the 120,000 disabled persons of Lanzhou, a city
which has a relatively underdeveloped economy and is frequently
hit by natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
In the first six months after the federation was formed, the
All-China Charity Federation donated 300,000 yuan (about 36,000 US
dollars) to a water conservation project in the city, and the
local urban cooperation bank aided the local children's welfare
institute with 200,000 yuan (about 24,000 US dollars) for the
rehabilitation of disabled youths.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, 31 enterprises and institutions have joined the
federation as group members, and a total of 129,300 yuan (about
15,500 US dollars) has been donated.  
</P>
</TEXT>
