<HEADLINE> Italy Provides Emergency Fund to Quake-Stricken Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 27 (Xinhua) -- The Italian government today
earmarked a special fund to cope with the emergency created by
Saturday's earthquakes and the subsequent reconstruction work.
</P>
<P>
The money will be provided in two separate programs.
</P>
<P>
Some 56 billion lire (33 million U.S. dollars) was allocated to
deal with the emergency and another 800 billion lire (471 million
dollars) was penciled into the 1998 budget bill for reconstruction
in the worst-hit regions of Umbria and Marche.
</P>
<P>
The quakes, measuring 5.5 and 5.6 on the Richter scale, killed
at least 11 people and left 5,000 homeless in central Italy. They
also severely damaged Assisi's magnificent 13th century Basilica
of St. Francis and other architectural treasures. 
</P>
