<HEADLINE> China Completes Statue of Its Ancestor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, September 28 (Xinhua) -- China has completed the first
large-scale bronze statue commemorating Shun, one of the ancestors
of the Chinese nation, in Jinan, capital of east China's
Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
A Hong Kong billionaire donated one million yuan (about 125,000
US dollars) to build the 3.5-ton statue in an area of 400 square
meters.
</P>
<P>
The four-meter high statue was designed by Fan Zeng, a
nationally-known painter, and was placed at the foot of Qianfo
Mountain in Jinan where Shun once worked as a farmer.
</P>
<P>
Shun was the legendary leader of the tribal union in eastern
parts of China some 5,000 years ago. He is worshiped as a hero of
the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
Information about Shun is included in the Records of the
Historian by Sima Qian of the Han Dynasty, a famous Chinese
historian in the first century B.C., saying that Shun once lived
in what is now the city of Jinan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
