<HEADLINE> Gugelmin Sets Record for Fastest Qualifying Lap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian Mauricio
Gugelmin registered the fastest qualifying lap in motor racing
history in California on Saturday with a speed of 387.748
kilometers per hour.
</P>
<P>
Driving a Reynard Indy car powered by a Mercedes-Benz
turbocharged V8 engine, the Formula One veteran was even faster
during the morning's unofficial practice for Sunday's California
500 with a lap of 389.982 kph.
</P>
<P>
Arie Luyendyk of the Netherlands set the previous record of
382.930 kph during qualifying for the 1996 Indy 500 in the rival
IRL series.
</P>
<P>
Vasser, driving a Reynard Honda, registered a lap of 384.980
kph and Herta, with 382.836 kph in a Reynard Ford, also bettered
the old record.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's 500-mile (804 kilometers) race on the California
Speedway is the 17th and last race of the series. 
</P>
