<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Historians Say Ancient Chinese History Needs Rewriting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, September 28 (Xinhua) -- China has a history of 10,000
years of civilization rather than 5,000 years, some historians
have announced.
</P>
<P>
China's historical framework was built around "The Historical
Records", written by Sima Qian, a famous historian of the first
century B.C. But now, 2,000 years later, there have been new
discoveries in archaeology, anthropology, and folklore, giving
ancient history a different look, according to historians from
both sides of the Taiwan Straits attending a recent seminar on
Chinese history in Hainan Province.
</P>
<P>
Shi Shi, 75, a famous Chinese historian, said: "Sima Qian, who
was restricted by limited historical materials and knowledge,
built an ancient historical framework that was not quite in
accordance with historical reality," and offers some proposals for
a new Chinese historical framework.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese nation has a history of 10,000 years rather than
5,000 years, he said, and archaeological studies have proven
that Chinese civilization originated at least 9,000 years ago,
long before Huang Di, who is commonly recognized as the earliest
ancestor of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
He said that the origins of Chinese civilization are not
monistic, but pluralistic, and that it was not a single farming
nation and that the Huanghe River Valley is not the only
birthplace of the Chinese civilization. The Yangtze River and the
Huanghe River are both places of Chinese civilization's origins.
</P>
<P>
He used Guyue People, who lived in south China in ancient
times, as an example. They were typical maritime persons who
fished on the sea 7,000 years ago and created the oldest sea
civilization in the world.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that we should not value north China above
south China in historical studies. The maritime civilization and
farming civilization of ancient China both originated in south
China and so we should pay more attention to studies of ethnic
groups in south China.
</P>
<P>
A new ancient historical framework is an important task, one
that can help us better understand our ancestors and our nation,
Shi said.
</P>
<P>
"Sima Qian dared to write a history of 2,600 years with only
reliable historical materials of 700 years. If we dare not go one
step beyond the framework built by Sima Qian after we have gotten
reliable historical materials of 3,400 years and relics from 7,000
to 8,000 years, we will be laughed at by him," he
concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
