<HEADLINE> Coetzer Gives Hingis Season's Third Defeat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Amanada Coetzer of South
Africa gave world number one Martina Hingis her third defeat of
the season at the Leipzig Open tennis tournament on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Coetzer, ranked sixth in the world, beat Hingis 6-4, 4-6, 7-6
(7-3) to move into Sunday's final of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Coetzer almost let the match slip against Hingis as the
17-year-old world number one fought back from 3-0 to 3-3 in the
final set.
</P>
<P>
But Coetzer held on her nerve and won the set after taking the
tiebreaker 7-3.
</P>
<P>
Hingis' other defeats of the season came in the French Open
final against Croatian Iva Majoli and to American Lindsay
Davenport in Los Angeles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
