<HEADLINE> One Killed in Costa Rica Planes Collision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Two light planes collided
today in mid-air in Matina de Limon, east of San Jose, killing one
pilot dead and injuring the other, the Costa Rican Red Cross said
today.
</P>
<P>
Two Tiaws light planes were preparing to start spraying banana
plantations when for reasons not yet determined they collided in
mid-air.
</P>
<P>
The dead was identified as Carlos Manuel Franchesqui, 60, who
piloted one of the planes. the other pilot, Jorge Araya, 44, is in
a hospital.
</P>
<P>
Investigation has been launched into the causes of the fatal
air mishap.
</P>
<P>
There have been nine air accidents in Costa Rica since 1995.
</P>
</TEXT>
